Create Chat Proxy Lambda Function
📌 Overview

This Lambda function acts as a secure backend bridge between:

Frontend → API Gateway → Lambda → Bedrock Agent

It:

Invokes Bedrock Agent
Processes response
Returns output to frontend

🪜 Step-by-Step Implementation

🔹 Step 1 — Create Lambda Function
Open AWS Console → Lambda
Click Create function
Select:
Author from scratch

🔹 Step 2 — Basic Configuration

Fill the following details:

Function Name:
BedrockAgentChatProxy
Runtime:
Python 3.12
Architecture:
x86_64

🔹 Step 3 — Attach Execution Role
Scroll to Permissions
Click Change default execution role
Select:
Use an existing role
Choose:
BedrockAgentChatProxyRole

👉 (Ensure this role has:)

BedrockAgentInvokePolicy
AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole

🔹 Step 4 — Add Lambda Code
Go to Code tab
Remove default code
Copy full code from chat proxy code file and Paste into Lambda editor
Click Deploy

🔹 Step 5 — Configure Lambda Settings
Go to:
Configuration → General configuration
Click Edit
Set values:
Memory:
512 MB
Timeout:
30 seconds
Click Save

🔹 Step 6 — Configure Environment Variables
📌 Why Required?

Lambda needs:

Agent ID → which agent to call
Alias ID → which version to use
🪜 Add Variables
Go to:
Configuration → Environment variables
Click Edit → Add environment variable
🔸 Variable 1 — AGENT_ID
Key:
AGENT_ID
Value:
👉 Your Bedrock Agent ID
📍 How to Get Agent ID
Open Amazon Bedrock
Click Agents
Select your agent
Copy Agent ID

Example:

HMYXWRJWOG
🔸 Variable 2 — AGENT_ALIAS_ID
Key:
AGENT_ALIAS_ID
Value:
👉 Your Alias ID
📍 How to Create & Get Alias ID
Open your agent
Go to Aliases tab
👉 If alias not created:
Click Create alias
Enter name:
production
Select:
Create a new version and associate it
Click Create
👉 After creation:

Scroll down → copy Alias ID

Example:

RZZA9Z0DXI

🔹 Step 7 — Save Environment Variables

👉 Click Save


✅ Final Result

✔ Lambda function created
✔ IAM role attached
✔ Bedrock Agent connected
✔ Environment variables configured

🧠 Important Notes
Agent ID = Agent identity
Alias ID = Version control
Lambda uses both to call correct agent

🚀 Summary Flow
User → Frontend → API Gateway → Lambda → Bedrock Agent → Response
